text: Isabey (or Isa Bey) may refer to : ; Persons * Eugène Isabey (1803–1886), French painter, draftsman and printmaker * Jean-Baptiste Isabey (1767–1855), French painter born at Nancy * Michaël Isabey (born 1975), French football midfielder ; Places in Turkey * the modern Anatolian site of the Ancient town and former Roman bishopric of Lunda (Asia Minor), now a Latin Catholic titular see * Isabey Mosque or İsa Bey Mosque, on the outskirts of the Ayasluğ Hills at Selçuk, İzmir, named after it builder, an Aydinid from the Anatolian Seljuk beyliks (1374–1375) == See also == * Isabeau
title: Isabey
